Class LocalizableAction

  • java.lang.Object
    • javax.swing.AbstractAction
      • hr.fer.zemris.java.hw11.jnotepadpp.elements.LocalizableAction
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ILocalizationListener, java.awt.event.ActionListener, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, java.util.EventListener, javax.swing.Action
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ChangeCaseAction, CloseAction, CloseAllAction, CopyAction, CutAction, DeleteAction, ExitAction, LanguageSelectAction, NewFileAction, OpenAction, PasteAction, SaveAction, SaveAsAction, SelectAllAction, SortAction, StatisticsAction

    public abstract class LocalizableAction
extends javax.swing.AbstractAction
implements ILocalizationListener
    AbstractAction intended for use with ILocalizationProvider implementing classes.

    Reads from them using getTranslation() method. Requires the children classes to implement getDescriptionKey() and getNameKey() to work properly. If localization is not used, it is better to use AbstractAction since this has no other benefits other than localization adaptation.

    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Juraj Pejnovic
    See Also:
    ILocalizationProvider, ILocalizationListener, AbstractAction, Notepad, Serialized Form
